28/09/2010
SARAJEVO, Bosnia and Herzegovina (BiH) -- European Parliament (EP) member Jelko Kacin said on Monday (September 27th) that BiH can expect EU visa-free regimes to kick off the new year. At a press conference in Sarajevo, Kacin voiced confidence that visa requirements for BiH and Albania will be scrapped as of January 1st. Kacin also said that the EP Committee on Civil Liberties, Justice and Home Affairs will discuss the issue on October 6th. (Fena, BHRT, sarajevo-x.com - 27/09/10)
